Spec: SpecDD Test Skill

Purpose:
  Guide agents in deriving, adding, updating, or assessing focused tests from active SpecDD behavior.

Owns:
  ./specdd-test/SKILL.md.ejs
  ./specdd-test/agents/openai.yaml

Must:
  Identify test authority from the nearest relevant spec before editing tests.
  Derive test cases from applicable contract sections and scenarios.
  Derive cases from applicable `Must`, `Scenario`, `Handles`, `Returns`, `Raises`, `Tasks`, and `Done when` entries.
  Prefer the smallest tests that prove specified behavior.
  Test observable behavior, not wording in the spec.
  Cover forbidden behavior when it can regress silently.
  Add regression tests for confirmed bugs.
  Run the relevant project test command when available.
  Report which spec entries each test covers and specified behavior that still lacks verification.

Must not:
  Add broad test harnesses unless the active specs or project convention require them.
  Edit tests when test-file authority is unclear.
  Treat tests as a source for new behavior outside active specs.
  Overfit tests to spec wording instead of observable behavior.

Depends on:
  ../fragments/bootstrap-resolution.md.ejs
  ../fragments/spec-chain-resolution.md.ejs
